  ---
  Recommended Phased Approach

  Phase 1 (Low-cost, 3 months): Foundation

  - aashrayReady flag on listings — hosts opt-in
  - ORGANIZATION role — NGO accounts with case workers
  - Extended stay bookings (30-360 days, monthly billing)
  - Alternative ID types (UNHCR cert, LTV, FRO registration)
  - NGO invoice-based payment (bank transfer)
  - Target: 50 listings, 3 NGOs, 20 families housed

  Phase 2 (Months 4-9): Scale

  - New case-service — refugee profiles, placement tracking, integration milestones
  - Smart matching (family size vs capacity, proximity to schools/hospitals)
  - Language expansion (Arabic, Dari, Burmese, Tamil)
  - Host guarantee fund (damage protection, NGO-funded)
  - Public impact dashboard

  Phase 3 (Months 10-18): Global

  - Multi-currency payments (Wise/Stripe for international NGOs)
  - Emergency rapid response mode (geo-fenced, one-click activation)
  - International pilot (Bangladesh or Uganda)
  - CSR portal for Indian companies (Section 135, 80G receipts)
  - White-label SaaS for other NGOs

